metadata.name: Fuji San's lava flow | Japan
metadata.description:
Japan’s Mount Fuji is an active volcano about 100 km southwest of Tokyo. Commonly called “Fuji-san,” it’s the country’s tallest peak, at 3,776 meters.

This photo was taken in Japan, January 2020 ... and then turned into a life.

#1-Fuji from series of:   ...جور دیگر باید دید...
